    • Method Detail

      • getTrackingLegs

        public void getTrackingLegs(Map<String,Object> params,
                   ISirqulCallback<ListResponse<LegResponse>> callback)
        Retrieve tracking data to be able to show where a user has been.

        Target API Endpoint: /tracking/search

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        • SirqulKeys.ownerId of type Long
          the account id of the person the user wants to tracking data for
        • SirqulKeys.startDate of type Long
          the start date in (UTC milliseconds) to filter the tracking results. If no startDate is passed in, the last 30 days will be returned.
        • SirqulKeys.endDate of type Long
          the end date in (UTC milliseconds) to filter the tracking results
        • SirqulKeys.tags of type String
          filter results by tag
        • SirqulKeys.getLastPoint of type Boolean
          gets the last known location of the user
        SirqulResponse subclass type:
        • ListResponse<LegResponse> on valid response, or SirqulResponse with error message
        Parameters:
        params - the Map<String, Object> containing the parameters, both required and any optional ones you wish to send through to this api.
        callback - an optional ISirqulCallback instance that handles your response from this Sirqul API call. With this, API responses are automatically checked for validity or invalidity, whether it was null entirely, and to throw a SirqulException for any and all Exception's that may have occurred. Each of these cases are broken up into separate interface methods. If you foresee yourself needing to handle all cases, it's recommended you simply instantiate a new ISirqulCallback instance, which will force you to implement all methods. If you really only care about one or a few of them, you can use the SirqulCallback class, which you can optionally override any of those same interface methods. If you wish to ignore any response, simply pass in null for this.
        See Also:
        TrackingApiBase.getTrackingLegs(...)

      • saveTrackingLegs

        public void saveTrackingLegs(Map<String,Object> params,
                    ISirqulCallback<SirqulResponse> callback)
        Send tracking points to be able to generate pathing data.

        Target API Endpoint: /tracking

        Available parameters for this api
        • SirqulKeys.accountId of type Long
          the account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required)
        • SirqulKeys.distance of type Double
          the total distance
        • SirqulKeys.duration of type Long
          the total duration
        • SirqulKeys.startLocation of type Location
          the location of the first point
        • SirqulKeys.startDate of type Long
          the start date (in UTC milliseconds) of the first point
        • SirqulKeys.endLocation of type Location
          the location of the last point
        • SirqulKeys.endDate of type Long
          the end date (in UTC milliseconds) of the last point
        • SirqulKeys.steps of type List<TrackingStep>
          JSON array of tracking vectors used for smoother pathing data.

          Format is:

         "endLat": 47.785834,

         "startDate": 1361840740845,
         "duration": 0
     },
     {
         "endLat": 47.785834,
         "endLng": -122.406417,
         "distance": 0,

         "startLng": -122.406417,
         "startDate": 1361840740845,
         "duration": 4999
